## 4. How to Run the System

For testing and continuing development, your teammate will need two terminals open:

**Terminal 1 (Start the Backend API):**
`uv run uvicorn fcrag.api.main:app --reload`

**Terminal 2 (Start the Frontend UI):**
`uv run streamlit run demo/app.py`

### Important Note on AI Models (GPU vs API)
The system has an auto-detect feature for the AI model it uses:
- **Tier 2 (API - Recommended):** If you set the `HF_TOKEN` environment variable, it will use the HuggingFace Inference API. This is the fastest and easiest way to run it.
  - Windows: `set HF_TOKEN=your_token_here`
- **Tier 1 (Local GPU):** If you do NOT provide an `HF_TOKEN`, the system will check if you have an NVIDIA GPU. If you do, it will attempt to download and run the model locally. *Note: This requires significant VRAM.*
- **Tier 3 (Template Fallback):** If you don't have a GPU and don't provide an API token, the system safely falls back to a template matching system so the app never crashes.

To force the system to use the lightweight fallback (ignoring your GPU), set:
`set FCRAG_LLM_TIER=3`
